                    UH    Mail Code  162    Office Hours  By appointment    CV  Davis CV February 2017     About  Lennard J. Davis is Distinguished Professor of Liberal Arts and Science. He is the author and editor of numerous books on disability and Deafness including Enforcing Normalcy, The Disability Studies Reader, and The End of Normal.     Selected Publications   Enforcing Normalcy: Disability, Deafness and the Body , Verso    Disability Studies Reader , Routledge    The End of Normal , University of Michigan Press    Obsession: A History , University of Chicago Press     Notable Honors  2002 - Guggenheim Fellowship, John Simon Guggenheim Foundation    Education  BA, English and Comparative Literature, Columbia University, 1970 MA and MPhil, English and Comparative Literature, Columbia University, 1971 PhD, English and Comparative Literature, Columbia University, 1976           Disability and Human Development    Back to main content           Admissions and Programs    Expand Admissions and Programs menu          Minor in Disability and Human Development    BS in Disability and Human Development    Expand BS in Disability and Human Development menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    Expand Applying menu          Transferring from another UIC program      After You Apply      MS in Disability and Human Development    PhD in Disability Studies    Expand PhD in Disability Studies menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Faculty    Meet Our Students      Assistive Technology Certificate    Expand Assistive Technology Certificate menu          What to Expect    Applying    Faculty    Assistive Technology Certificate FAQ      Disability Ethics Certificate    Expand Disability Ethics Certificate menu          What to Expect    Applying        Institute on Disability and Human Development    Community Partners    Expand Community Partners menu          Bodies of Work      Research Centers, Clinics and 